      "date": "2012-09-12 19:42:46.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\nI'm OK with the idea, but I'm not sure about the implementation.  I'm happy to be convinced to change my inspection with a clear explanation.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "ebbad4626eb6e55767ead7fece783c8b56aeaf0b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2012-09-12 19:47:27.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI think nlink is semantically belongs to namespace (from OSD point of view this is a regular attribute with no special meaning, I'd say).\n so it's managed by MDD. again we have to do trick in ldiskfs osd because of 16bit constraint.\n\nnlink=1 should make sense on ZFS being POSIX thing ?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "aa71aa0ca2e5549cb336f391c48c9e0021d2df91",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2012-09-12 19:48:56.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI'm going to try rmdir on a directory with nlink = 1 on zfs.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "9b5431220b52be176f5be3e9422d47882507ee1b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2012-09-13 05:58:12.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nchecked with the code, you're right:\n\nzfs_link_destroy()\n{\n\tint zp_is_dir = S_ISDIR(ZTOI(zp)->i_mode);\n...\n\n\t\tif (zp->z_links <= zp_is_dir) {\n\t\t\tzfs_panic_recover(\"zfs: link count on %lu is %u, \"\n\t\t\t    \"should be at least %u\", zp->z_id,\n\t\t\t    (int)zp->z_links, zp_is_dir + 1);\n\t\t\tzp->z_links = zp_is_dir + 1;\n\t\t}\n\n\ndo you think it'd be OK to set it to 2 and do not change ever.\ne2fsck will complain, but this should not be fatal ?\nnot very convenient though..",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
